<TITLE> Shakil, Alomgir made heads in two BCB committees </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 8 (bdnews24.com)  New members Shakil Kasem and Engineer Ghulam Mohammad Alomgir have been appointed heads in two separate committees of the Bangladesh Cricket Board Tuesday. Shakil, a former national cricketer, has been named head of the Game Development Committee in place of Col MA Latif, who resigned from the board recently. Alomgir, secretary of the Mohammedan Sporting Club's cricket committee, has been made chairman of the Cricket Committee of Dhaka Metropolis and Tournament Committee in place of Gazi Ashraf Hossain Lipu, who is chairman of the Cricket Operation. 
